==English==

===Etymology===

Coined by the President of the United States George W. Bush at a speech in Bentonville, Arkanssa on Nov. 6, 2000.  Not surprising considering his tendency to misuse and make up words. A combination of the words [[misunderstand]] and [[underestimate]], one supposes.

===Verb===
# To underestimate by failing to understand.
